    "body": "Ah, and fortunately ‚Äúhelp‚Äù is consistent on both. Just a shame that Windows doesn‚Äôt ship with a better paginator by default? üòä\n\n \n\n-Oliver \n\n \n\nFrom: Keith Hill <notifications@github.com> \nSent: Friday, March 22, 2019 11:15 AM\nTo: PowerShell/PowerShell <PowerShell@noreply.github.com>\nCc: Oliver Smith <oliver@kfs.org>; Author <author@noreply.github.com>\nSubject: Re: [PowerShell/PowerShell] Get-Help summary version (#9189)\n\n \n\nPotentially consider Pagination by default?\n\nThere is pagination if you use the man alias on Windows or the help function on Linux (since man already exists as a native util) e.g. man get-help. PowerShell even honors the PAGER environment variable. On Windows, I use less via $env:PAGER = \"less\".\n\n‚Äî\nYou are receiving this because you authored the thread.\nReply to this email directly, view it on GitHub <https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/issues/9189#issuecomment-475726388> , or mute the thread <https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AATtwawaek9ZcV2X07lwBMLZ1cewCzJzks5vZR21gaJpZM4cCZOJ> .\n\n",
